05246nam a22009015i 9783110255355DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20112011gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)979584489  a97831102553557 a10.1515/97831102553552doi  a(DE-B1597)123636  a(OCoLC)754713646  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aREL0060902bisacsh04a229/.22061 aMacatangay, Francis M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Wisdom Instructions in the Book of Tobit /cFrancis M. Macatangay. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2011] 4c©2011  a1 online resource (367 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aDeuterocanonical and Cognate Literature Studies ,x1865-1666 ;v120 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDespite the resurgence of scholarly interest in the Book of Tobit in recent years, an important aspect of this deuterocanonical book has been largely overlooked. Within it, there is an instruction manual for an effective way of being and living in exile, namely the wisdom instructions in Tobit 4. With glances at Tobit 12 and Tobit 14 where the wisdom instructions are repeated in shorter form, this monograph discusses the function of the wisdom discourse in the literary design of the narrative. Moreover, it examines how the wisdom instructions of Tobit demonstrate the vital role of the sapiential tradition in forming and maintaining Jewish identity in the Diaspora. Contextualizing the wisdom instructions not only within the narrative but also within the realities of Second Temple Judaism, it is argued that the author of Tobit saw the validity and employed the resources of the Jewish wisdom tradition in reinterpreting some of the traditional claims of covenant faith.Using the Sinaiticus as the textual basis of study, it shows that the lengthy wisdom lecture of Tobit displays an inner logic that structures the collection of seemingly unrelated sayings. The instructions reinterpret a major deuteronomic concern to remember the Lord always. For Tobit, the practice of righteousness, the practice of wise behavior, and the practice of prayer realize and concretize such remembrance. Addressed to those in the Dispersion, Tobit’s wisdom instructions are meant to foster and shape a distinct ethos of truth, righteousness and mercy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aDas Buch Tobit. 4aExegese. 4aExil. 4aJudentum des Zweiten Tempels. 4aNarrative Kritik. 4aWeisheit. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aBook of Tobit.  aExile.  aNarrative Criticism.  aSecond Temple Judaism.  aWisdom.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2011z978311026123308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2011z9783110261271oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311025534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311025535540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110255355423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110255355/original  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-1